\begin_layout Standard
Almost all the components have 
\shape italic
configuration parameters
\shape default
, used to tweak and customize their behavior.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The values of some parameters can be set up only at creation time and cannot
 change during the component lifetime; others have not this limitation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Some parameter is considered 
\shape italic
mandatory
\shape default
, that is some hard coded (
\shape italic
default
\shape default
) value need to be specified at component creation time, otherwise the component
 could fall back in a meaningless behavior.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At creation time, parameters are specified through the 
\shape italic
game configuration file
\shape default
 (usually 
\shape italic
game.xml
\shape default
)
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "chap:Game-configuration-file"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Any component parameter has these attributes:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\shape italic
name
\shape default
: it is chosen as self-documenting as possible, usually referring to the
 underlying logics or native component attributes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\shape italic
type
\shape default
: a parameter can have 
\shape italic
single
\shape default
 value or 
\shape italic
multiple
\shape default
 value
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\shape italic
default
\shape default
: the hard-coded specified value at creation time (only for mandatory parameters
) 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the 
\shape italic
API Documentation
\shape default
 
